ystem. Generally, a low level of viscosity ($\\alpha \\leq 2\\cdot10^{-3}$) is\nnecessary to allow the existence of such a feature. Including dust feedback the\nleading point L4 can dominantly capture dust for dust grains with an initial\nStokes number $\\leq 3.6\\cdot 10^{-2}$. The observational results suggest a\nnegligible effect of dust feedback since only one such feature has been\ndetected so far.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 16 Dec 2020 19:13:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-31"}
